Description: Inlay: head of a falcon in opaque white glass facing right. The eye is an opaque black disc outlined in orange. The conventionalized markings always present on the head of this bird, here in dark-blue glass, are separated by a small slice of banded mosaic glass. The companion piece, facing left, is in Cairo (32122). Both examples are probably the terminals of a 'wesekh' collar.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Temple of Hathor (Dendara), Temple of Hathor
Bibliographic references: Tait 1991 / Five Thousand Years of Glass (pl.61)
